OL,6,FHe added: "The difference tomorrow is
OL,7,Fthat it is not likely to be as warm
OL,8,Ffor Northern Ireland, Wales or
OL,9,FScotland.
OL,11,F"The really warm air will probably be
OL,12,Fconfined to southern and eastern parts
OL,13,Fof England, with temperatures expected
OL,14,Fto peak in central parts of the
OL,15,Fcountry at around 27C."
OL,17,FParts of the UK will be warm and humid
OL,18,Fin the morning before thunderstorms
OL,19,Fand heavy rain are expected in the
OL,20,Fafternoon.
