OL,6,FGogerddan in Wales saw 25.1C, while
OL,7,Ftemperatures in Northern Ireland
OL,8,Fpeaked at 23.8C in Magilligan.
OL,10,FTemperatures climbed steadily over the
OL,11,Fweek, with the previous record set on
OL,12,FThursday, with a peak of 24.6C in
OL,13,FLondon's St James's Park.
OL,15,FThe Royal Life Saving Society UK has
OL,16,Fwarned warmer weather is directly
OL,17,Flinked to an increase in fatal
OL,18,Fdrowning incidents.
